Ever Live Album |publisher=XLR8R |date=2008-03-24 |accessdate=2011-11-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080323095249/http://www.xlr8r.com/news/2008/03/les-savvy-fav-releases-first-eve |archivedate=2008-03-23 }}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n# Equestrian\n# Patty Lee\n# What Would Wolves Do?\n# Sweat Descends\n# Yawn Yawn Yawn\n# We'll Make A Lover Of You\n# The Year Before The Year 2000\n# The Lowest Bitter\n# Who Rocks The Party\n# Tim Speech\n# Hey Tonight (Creedence Clearwater Revival Cover)\n# Debaser (Pixies Cover)\n# Astro Zombies (Misfits Cover)\n# Sliver ([[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]] Cover)\n# Everybody's Gotta Live ([[Love (band)|Love]] Cover)\n\n==Credits==\nLes Savy Fav consists of:\n\n* Tim Harrington&nbsp;\u2013 singer\n* Seth Jabour&nbsp;\u2013 guitarist\n* [[Syd Butler]]&nbsp;\u2013 bassist\n* Harrison Haynes&nbsp;\u2013 drummer\n* Andrew Reuland&nbsp;\u2013 guitarist\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.frenchkissrecords.com/ French Kiss Records]\n\n[[Category:2008 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at the Bowery Ballroom]]\n[[Category:Les Savy Fav albums]]\n\n\n{{2010s-rock-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{one source|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = After the Balls Drop\n| type       = live\n| artist     = [[Les Savy Fav]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2008|04|29}}\n| recorded   = January 1, 2008\n| venue      = [[Bowery Ballroom]]<br />New York City, New York\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Rock music|Rock]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Frenchkiss Records|Frenchkiss]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/les-savy-fav-after-the-ball-drops-2496156179.html|title=Les Savy Fav: After the Balls Drop|date=April 30, 2008|website=PopMatters}}</ref>\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Let's Stay Friends]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = [[Root for Ruin]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n{{album reviews\n|rev1 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]